<TITLE> Kiron named AFC EC member </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 15 (bdnews24.com)  Mahfuza Akhter Kiron, the deputy chairman of the Bangladesh Football Federation's women's football committee, has been selected an executive member of the Asian Football Federation. The decision was made at the AFC executive committee meeting held in Malaysia on Wednesday, said a BFF press release. Besides, Harunur Rashid, the BFF executive member, has also been named a member of the AFC Organising Committee for Asian Cup 2011. Meanwhile, BFF president Kazi Salahuddin on Wednesday met All Indian Football Federation general secretary Robert Colaco in Malaysia in a bid to bring Indian clubs East Bengal and Mohan Bagan in the Bangabandhu Gold Cup to be held in Dhaka from October-November. Salahuddin told reporters by phone that he had a positive discussion with Colaco as well as representatives of other countries from where the BFF would like to bring the clubs. Colaco has agreed to send Indian sides to Bangladesh, but he had been struggling with the period of the tournament as the Indian professional football league was scheduled to get underway in Septembe
